{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All available connections will be closed immediately. Any connections still in use will be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"closed as soon as they are returned to the pool. Once closed, the pool can not be used to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"create new connections."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Connection pools must be closed before they deinitialize.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method shuts the pool down asynchronously. It may be invoked on any event loop. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"provided callback will be notified when shutdown is complete. It is invalid to allow a pool"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to deinitialize before it has fully shut down."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method promises explicitly as API contract not to invoke the callback before returning"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to its caller. It further promises the callback will not be invoked on any event loop"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"belonging to the pool."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any invocation of the callback represents a signal that the pool has fully shut"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"down. This is true even if the error parameter is non-"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"; errors are purely advisory."}]}],"style":"warning","type":"aside"}]}],"references":{"doc://co.pointfree.VaporRouting/documentation/AsyncKit/EventLoopGroupConnectionPool":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"EventLoopGroupConnectionPool","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/co.pointfree.VaporRouting\/documentation\/AsyncKit\/EventLoopGroupConnectionPool","kind":"symbol","title":"EventLoopGroupConnectionPool","role":"sym